 semantics. 'Constructions in Use' offers an alternative by proposing to let this legacy go. Instead, it argues that philosophical semantics is best off if it goes for an entirely use-based theory. This series explores issues of mental representation, linguistic structure and representation, and their interplay. The research presented in this series is grounded in the idea explored in the Collaborative Research Center 'The structure of representations in language, cognition and science' (SFB 991) that there is a universal format for the representation of linguistic and cognitive concepts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 4aconstruction grammar. 4aphilosophical semantics. 4aphilosophy of language. 4atruth-conditional semantics. 4ause-based semantics. 4ause-based theory. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aCognitive Semantics.  aCompositionality.  aConstruction Grammar.  aConstructionist Language Acquisition.  aConstructionist Primary Meaning.  aCooperative Context.  aDie Struktur von Repräsentationen in Sprache, Kognition und Wissenschaft.  aDisposition.  aDonald Davidson.  aFramework.  aGerhard Schurz.  aHana Filip.  aHeinrich-Heine-Universität Düsseldorf.  aHorwich.  aIntuitive Propositional Content.  aKnowledge Covary.  aLaura Kallmeyer.  aLinguistic-Philosophical Terminology.  aLiteral Interface.  aMalapropisms.  aMeaning Liberalism.  aMeaning.  aMultimodality.  aNon-Literal Interface.  aNovelty.  aPeter Indefrey.  aPragmatic.  aPrimary Meaning.  aRobert D. Van Valin, Jr.  aSFB 991.  aSebastian Löbner.  aSonderforschungsbereich 991.  aThe structu